This paper deals with natural language processing and word embeddings, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze and classify word semantics, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of semantic axes to capture nuanced word meanings, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper analyzes word sentiment, which is a common topic in social media analysis (cs.SI).
